==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Duodecimo
<hw>Du`o*dec"i*mo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>in
duodecimo</ets> in twelfth, fr. <ets>duodecimus twelfth</ets>,
<ets>fr</ets>. <ets>duodecim</ets> twelve. See <er>Dozen</er>.]</ety>
<def>Having twelve leaves to a sheet; <as>as, a <ex>duodecimo</ex> from,
book, leaf, size, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Duodecimo</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Duodecimo
<hw>Du*o*dec"i*mo</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Duodecimos</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <def>A book consisting of
sheets each of which is folded into twelve leaves; hence, indicating,
more or less definitely, a size of a book; -- usually written 12mo or
12⟦deg⟧.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Duodecuple</ent>⟦br⟧
